args: WHOOOA! Dragons sure are fast! Prancer,\nhold on tight to that sack of goodies!
WHAT WAS THAT?\nCan't hear you over the wind, Boss!
(Getting all the presents took longer than\nI'd planned, but this dragon ride should\nmake up the difference.)
(Help with the presents,\nplus a dragon to airlift them...\nI owe {player_name} a debt.)
Gah! The wind blew the sack of\npresents away!
What'd I JUST say, you nimrod?!
I'll hop off and round them up. You two\nhead to the village and get ready for\nour deliveries.
Hop off...a moving dragon?! But that's\nmadness, good sir! You'll just be dashed\nto pieces on the ground!
I'll do anything to make those kids smile.\nLeave this to me. You go on ahead.
No way! He JUMPED!\nUh, Boss, what do we do now?\nAre we gonna do what he said?
No, dingus! We're thieves! Who cares\nabout a bunch of sad little kids and\ntheir...big, tearful puppy-dog eyes...
Okay, FINE. We'll do what he says,\nbut if he doesn't show up, we're robbing\nthe place blind like I planned!
(The wind has carried the presents quite\na ways away. I wonder if I can even catch\nup before I'll have to open my chute...)
(All right, I grabbed the sack.\nTime to open my parachute!)
(A malfunction? Think, Victor...\nLanding at this speed will surely kill me.)
(I'm barreling faster by the second.\nNo time to think. I need to cushion\nmy landing somehow!)
Phew. That seems to have dulled my\nimpact just enough to save my skin.
The presents are intact too. \nI must hurry to the village, andâ€”hm?
Ah. These must be the fiends\nthe villagers mentioned.
Guess we're in for a melee!
Time's up, Boss. I'm sure our hulkin'\nfriend's a person-sized puddle of goo\nby now. No sense waiting anymore.
The longer we wait, the less time we'll\nhave for robbing. C'mon, Boss!
...I guess you're right. It's a shame we\nwon't be able to make him our scapegoat,\nbut I suppose we don't have much choice.
We're back to our original plan: pose\nas Saint Starfall and clean this village out!
I knew you were up to something,\nbut I didn't expect it'd be quite so vile.
Hmph. No use pretending anymore.\nWell? What are you going to do? \nBrutalize us and toss us out in the cold?
Later, if you like. But first, I still\nneed help delivering these presents.
No way! We's thieves! Robbing folks\nis our cauliflower... Er, our collie...
Our calling, numskull.\nAnd you're quite right.
This is the only way we know how to live.\nWe're too broke to be giving things away!
Is robbing people REALLY your heart's\ncalling?

Hearing those kids' wishes, didn't part
of you want to make them come true?
To see the joy on their faces as they
opened the presents they so badly wanted?

There's a child in this village who I want
to make happy, you see. He heard Saint
Starfall wasn't coming this year and
completely shut himself away.
It's my fault he's going through that.\nSo to make amends, I'm doing something\nthat's...outside of my comfort zone.
Your scheme will rob innocent children\nof what little joy I can give them this year.\nBut you can still choose a different path.
A thief can't make these kids happy.\nBut Saint Starfall can. Which will you be?
Of course we WANNA make those kids\nhappy, but what choice do we have?!
Bad case o' the blues ain't never killed\nnobody. If thieving keeps US alive, what's\nit matter if we make a few kids cry?
If you truly think you won't regret it,\nthen so be it. But I know you will.
I'm not so unfeeling that I can let people\nwalk down the wrong path uncontested.
If you need it, I can pay you a little for\nyour labor out of my own pocket.
So you have to choose. Will you steal\njoy, or will you give it?
I...guess we can make an exception,\nit being Dragonyule and all. We'll\nhelp you make those kids happy.
If the boss says so, then I'll help too.\nI'm not a thief tonightâ€”I'm Saint Starfall!
You and I both, my friend.
Hello? Is...\nIs that you, Saint Starfall?
Hello, Daniil. Sorry to wake you.
It's really you!\nDid you bring me a present?!
But I'm afraid I can't give you\nwhat you asked for this year.
Why not?! I've been so good!\nWhy can't you do it?!
I just want to see my dad again!\nPlease!
I'm sorry, Daniil. Your father is no longer\nhere in this world. I can't bring him back.
No! He said he'd come home!\nSaint Starfall came, so why can't Dad?!
Daniil, I know it can't take your\nfather's place, but...this is for you.
